China Wealth Fund, Harvard Buy Shares in VTB, Vedomosti Reports

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-02-16T06:06:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/china-wealth-fund-harvard-buy-shares-in-vtb-vedomosti-reports.html
China Investment Corp. and  Harvard
University  were among investors that bought shares in VTB
Group, Russia’s second-largest lender, Vedomosti reported,
citing Herbert Moos, the bank’s deputy chairman.  The Chinese sovereign wealth fund bought $100 million of
VTB stock, in its first big investment in Russia, the newspaper
said. The largest buyer in the placement of 10 percent of the
state-run bank’s shares was  Assicurazioni Generali SpA , which
invested $300 million, and private-equity fund TPG Capital LP
bought shares worth $100 million, Vedomosti reported.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Henry Meyer in Moscow at 
 hmeyer4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net . 